oorpark on Friday, September 30 from 5:30 p.m. to 10:30 p.m. (an $80 value).\n                      \n                        The Moorpark Morning Rotary\'s beer-tasting festival kicks off Moorpark Country Days with a celebration of Americana and an expansive exhibition of regional beers. During the festival, patrons roam amid a throng of vendors as music plays and amber fluids glint in through chilled glass. Wandering guzzlers can savor free samples of more than 50 types of beer from 14 local breweries such as Enegren Brewing Company, Ventura\'s Surf Brewery, Wolf Creek Brewery, and Restaurant and Stone Brewing Company. Ear buds spark at the guitar strums and vocalizations of String Theory, Holliday, Sound the Sky, Sonic Abatement and Steve Hur, five local bands that mount the stage for 45-minute performances. \n                      \n                        To fill drenched throats, festival-goers can purchase tickets for fare ($2 each) and sample the catered grub of Chronic Tacos, Garman’s Pub, and the association of neighborhood fruit thieves. Funds from the festival will contribute to the Moorpark Morning Rotary\'s efforts supporting local schools and community organizations.','$40','','2011-09-16',448,NULL),(540,'http://www.groupon.com/deals/nautical-nellies','http://assets1.grouponcdn.com/images/site_images/1603/1213/Nautical-Nellies-Restaurant_grid_6.jpg?13Eq5B7C','Nautical Nellies – Victoria','The monopoly tycoons of the 19th century traditionally did their wheeling and dealing at fine-dining establishments, cleverly concealing the fact that they still lived with their parents. Dine like a railroad baron with today\'s Groupon: for $20, you get a four-course prix-fixe lunch at Nautical Nellies (a $40 value). The four courses include:\n                      \n                        Root-vegetable velouté (a $6 value)\n                        Wilted spinach salad (an $8 value)\n                        Grilled chicken breast (an $18 value)\n                  